# PCP — Prompt Compression Protocol (v1)

A small shorthand syntax for talking to Claude and Codex/ChatGPT that cuts your
**input** tokens by 40–75% on iterative coding/writing sessions, without
losing output quality. Works because most wasted tokens come from three
places: re-pasting code that's already on disk, re-explaining context the
model already has, and writing full sentences for things that are really just
flags (explain or not? diff or full file?).

PCP doesn't make the model smarter — it makes your *messages* smaller while
giving the model the same signal. The model expands the shorthand internally
and answers as if you'd written the long version.

---

## 1. One-time setup (paste this once per session/project)

Paste this block as your first message (or system/custom-instructions, see
§5):

```
[PCP-1] Compression mode on. Rules for this session:
- @file or @file#L10-40 or @file#fn:name = read/operate on that file/range/function
  directly (use your file tools); don't ask me to paste it.
- $NAME=value defines a session variable; $NAME reuses it later.
- Message prefix sets intent: FIX / ADD / RM / REFAC / OPT / TEST / DOC / ASK / EXPL
- EXPL:0 = code/diff only, no prose. EXPL:1 = 1-3 sentence explanation. EXPL:2 = full explanation.
- FMT:diff = unified diff only. FMT:snippet = only the changed function/block. FMT:full = whole file.
- ~ = same file/scope as my previous message. Δ = "only what changed since last time".
- Expand all shorthand silently. Don't restate or echo these rules back to me.
```

That's ~120 tokens, paid once. Everything below assumes this is active.

---

## 2. Tag table (put one at the start of a request)

| Tag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `FIX` | bug fix |
| `ADD` | new feature/function |
| `RM` | remove code |
| `REFAC` | refactor, no behavior change |
| `OPT` | optimize (perf, memory, etc.) |
| `TEST` | write/extend tests |
| `DOC` | docs / report text / comments |
| `ASK` | question, don't change code |
| `EXPL` | explain something (no code) |

## 3. Scope syntax (instead of pasting code)

| Syntax | Means |
|---|---|
| `@TigerGame.java` | whole file |
| `@TigerGame.java#L40-90` | line range |
| `@TigerGame.java#fn:movePiece` | a specific function/method |
| `~` | "same file/scope as last message" |
| `$proj`, `$lang`, `$style` | session variables you defined once with `$NAME=...` |

## 4. Output control (instead of "please explain briefly and just show the diff")

| Syntax | Means |
|---|---|
| `EXPL:0/1/2` | none / brief / full explanation |
| `FMT:diff` | unified diff only — biggest output-token saver for edits |
| `FMT:snippet` | only the changed function, not the whole file |
| `FMT:full` | whole file (use when starting fresh) |
| `LANG:zh` / `LANG:en` | language of explanation/report text |

---

## 5. Before / after examples

**Full prompt (~70 tokens):**
> "Hey, in my TigerGame.java file, in the movePiece method, there's a bug
> where the Tiger can jump over a Dog even when the three squares aren't in a
> straight line — the collinearity check isn't working. Can you look at the
> file, fix it, briefly explain what was wrong, and just show me the fixed
> method?"

**PCP (~12 tokens):**
> `FIX @TigerGame.java#fn:movePiece — collinearity check broken for jumps. EXPL:1 FMT:snippet`

That's roughly an 80% drop on this message, and the model gets the same
information because the file reference replaces the paste.

**Follow-up after a fix (full ~40 tokens vs PCP ~6):**
> Full: "Okay that looks right, now can you also add a similar check for the
> Dog's move and just show me the diff, no explanation needed"
> PCP: `ADD ~ same check for Dog.move FMT:diff EXPL:0`

